ITV.Tour.de.France.2014.Stage.2.Live.PDTV.x264-NX

Sunday 6th July 2014 ITV4
10:30am to 5pm Live

The second of the two Yorkshire stages is 198km from York to Sheffield, passing through the hilly terrain of the Peak District. With 3,400m of climbing, the stage has been heralded as a British version of the Liege-Bastogne-Liege classic, with the notorious climb of Holme Moss 50km from the finish. Presented by Gary Imlach, with guests Chris Boardman and David Millar, commentary by Phil Liggett and Paul Sherwen, and reporter Ned Boulting.
